TL;DR

Certstream is an intellegence feed that gives you real-time updates from the Certificate Transparency List network, allowing you to build tools that react to new certifiates being issued in real time. We do all the hard work of aggregating and parsing, and give you simple libraries that enable you to do awesome things with minimal effort.

It's our way of saying "thank you" to the amazing security community in general, as well as a good way to give people a taste of the sort of intellegence feeds that are powering our flagship product - PhishFinder.

CertStream CLI

The default invocation of certstream connects to the network and outputs a greppable format.

It also supports substring matching and writing found matches to a file.

Library Usage

We've written simple integrations for most popular/major languages out there. If you want to contribute more please visit our Github and open a ticket!
